This SQ joins the BCI table to the BCA table, for specific INV_ELIG_DT values (see session SQ value). This mapping is used in two workflows - WF1 - runs during the time that a monthly period claim lock code (RCIT_LOCK_CNTL) is OPEN. Executes in Maestro. WF2 - runs with other period close activities that is initiated from the RCI Manager periods lock maintenance screen. Executes in Process Controller.
Filter - Claims for the period specified (open or just closed) Aetna primary payers (only way to determine Aetna claims even without Rebate IDs assigned) Model Type Code - for partitioning, as the payer filter would only allow Aetna primary regardless. Claim Batch Date >= 1/1/2014 (leftover code from original Risk Code update) Null field combinations (OR) - 1. Risk code is null (perform lookup on RPSDM GRP_CDD data) 2. Both the RX Plan ID and Contracted State Code are null (perform lookup on RPSDM GRP_CDD) 3. All three drug list names are NULL (perform lookup on EDM Aetna PBA table)
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_RCIT_BASE_CLM_APC

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT BCA.CLM_GID, BCA.BTCH_GID, BCI.INV_ELIG_DT, BCI.MODEL_TYP_CD, BCI.PRD_ID, BCI.RBEL_CLNT_CD, BCI.NRE_CLM_CD, BCA.RISK_CD, BCI.RX_PLAN_ID, BCI.PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM , BCI.STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM, BCI.QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM, BCI.CTRC_ST_CD, BCI.EXTL_LVL1_ID, BCI.EXTL_LVL2_ID, BCI.EXTL_LVL3_ID, BCI.DSPN_DT FROM VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_APC BCA, VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV BCI, VRAP.RCIV_TRNSL_CD_LKP LKP WHERE BCI.CLM_GID = BCA.CLM_GID AND BCI.BTCH_GID = BCA.BTCH_GID AND BCI.INV_ELIG_DT >=$$MIN_MTH_END_DT AND BCI.MODEL_TYP_CD IN( 'T','H') AND (BCA.RISK_CD IS NULL OR (BCI.RX_PLAN_ID IS NULL AND BCI.CTRC_ST_CD IS NULL) OR (BCI.PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM IS NULL AND BCI.STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM IS NULL AND BCI.QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM IS NULL)) AND BCA.BTCH_DT >= '01/01/2014' AND LKP.EXTL_SRC_CD = BCI.EXTL_SRC_CD AND LKP.EXTL_LVL1_ID = BCI.EXTL_LVL1_ID AND LKP.CORP_CD = 2 AND BCI.DSPN_DT BETWEEN LKP.CARRIER_EFF_DT AND LKP.CARRIER_EXP_DT AND INSTR(LKP.ALL_CDS,'|AETNA_CDD|') > 0 WITH UR

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION:
ITPR009414 Aetna PBA/Medical Indicator/Missing Risk code Perform logic on the source data to determine if the source data should be changed, as per the project requirements.
-Do not allow code to replace pre-existing values. -RX Plan Code and Contracted State Code are considered paired - they will either have both, or none. -Drug List names are condidered together as well, however, can be populated in any combination of the three. -Risk Code is completely separate from the others.
If either the RX Plan Code or the Contracted State Code have a value and the other is null (should not occur), this code will not populate the NULL value of the two.
If any of the three drug list names are populated, no attempt at updating any of them for that claim will be made.
If the Risk code is null, and the above populated, an attempt at populating the risk code will be made.
It was found during testing that the Teradata source could have non-NULL, non-space, no-length values, which was accounted for in the evaluation of the Teradata field values.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_Format_lkp

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If the input PBA fields is not equal to the PBA fields from the lookup, set the BCI_FLAG to be 1. '~NULL~' is assigned to handle NULL value from the source
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION:
iif(((IIF(ISNULL(v_PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM),'~NULL~',v_PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM)<> IIF(ISNULL(PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM),'~NULL~',PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM) ) OR (IIF(ISNULL(v_STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM),'~NULL~',v_STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM) <> IIF(ISNULL(STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM),'~NULL~',STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM) )
OR (IIF(ISNULL(v_QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM),'~NULL~',v_QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM) <> IIF(ISNULL(QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM ),'~NULL~',QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM ) )
OR ( IIF(ISNULL(v_CTRC_ST_CD),'~~',v_CTRC_ST_CD) <>IIF(ISNULL(CTRC_ST_CD ),'~~',CTRC_ST_CD ) )
OR (IIF(ISNULL(v_RX_PLAN_ID),'~NULL~',v_RX_PLAN_ID) <> IIF(ISNULL(RX_PLAN_ID ),'~NULL~',RX_PLAN_ID ) )),1,0)
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: v_BCI_FLAG

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF((v_BCI_FLAG=1 and PRD_ID != 'HOLD' AND NRE_CLM_CD = '0' AND RBEL_CLNT_CD = '1'),1,0)
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: CIE_FLAG

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Unconnected lookup pulls 'GRP CDD DATA' from GRP_CDD_AETNA_BASE Table based on CAG values and the dispense date.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_GRP_CDD_DATA

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup Sql Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT RPAD(TRIM(CDD.RISK_CD),1,' ')||RPAD(TRIM(CDD.CTRC_ST_NM),2,' ')||RPAD(TRIM(CDD.PLAN_ID),10,' ') AS GRP_CDD_DATA, CDD.EXTL_LVL1_ID AS EXTL_LVL1_ID, CDD.EXTL_LVL2_ID AS EXTL_LVL2_ID, CDD.EXTL_LVL3_ID AS EXTL_LVL3_ID, CDD.EFF_DT AS EFF_DT, CDD.END_DT AS END_DT FROM RPS.GRP_CDD_AETNA_BASE CDD WHERE CDD.STAT_CD = 'A' AND -- ACTIVE ROWS CDD.EFF_DT <= SYSDATE AND -- EFFECTIVE DATE OF ROW IS NOT FUTURE (CDD.PLAN_ID IS NOT NULL AND CDD.CTRC_ST_NM IS NOT NULL AND CDD.RISK_CD IS NOT NULL) -- DONT PULL BACK EMPTY ROWS --SQL Override

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup condition
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: EXTL_LVL1_ID = EXTL_LVL1_ID_In AND EXTL_LVL2_ID = EXTL_LVL2_ID_In AND EXTL_LVL3_ID = EXTL_LVL3_ID_In AND EFF_DT <= DSPN_DT_In AND END_DT >= DSPN_DT_In

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Update Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: UPDATE VRAP.RCIT_CLM_INV_ELIG SET RX_PLAN_ID = :TU.RX_PLAN_ID, PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM = :TU.PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM, STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM = :TU.STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM, QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM = :TU.QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM, CTRC_ST_CD = :TU.CTRC_ST_CD WHERE CLM_GID = :TU.CLM_GID AND INV_ELIG_DT = :TU.INV_ELIG_DT AND MODEL_TYP_CD = :TU.MODEL_TYP_CD

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Update Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: UPDATE VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV SET RX_PLAN_ID = :TU.RX_PLAN_ID, PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM = :TU.PCERT_DRUG_LIST_NM, STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM = :TU.STEP_THRPY_DRUG_LIST_NM, QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM = :TU.QTY_LMT_DRUG_LIST_NM, CTRC_ST_CD = :TU.CTRC_ST_CD WHERE CLM_GID = :TU.CLM_GID AND MODEL_TYP_CD = :TU.MODEL_TYP_CD AND INV_ELIG_DT = :TU.INV_ELIG_DT

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION:
This Get Period Date Range session will be used to identify claim periods where the period is Open and at the same time the APC period that the claim period resides in, is also Open.
Builds an output parameter file for the next session to use when determining which subset of claims to use (by period).
